  "text": "Finally, in terms of more general solutions, Chase and Meiklejohn abstract CT into the general idea of a \"transparency overlay\" [CITATION_1] and prove its security. Similarly, CoSi [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] is a general consensus mechanism that shares our goal of providing transparency even in the face of MitM attacks and thus avoids gossiping, but requires setting up a distributed set of \"witnesses\" that is free of Sybils. This is a deployment overhead that we avoid.",
